# Project Operating Instructions

These rules take priority over default behavior unless the user explicitly overrides them.

## Language

- Always communicate with the user in Arabic.
- All analysis, progress updates, findings, plans, explanations, and reports must be written in Arabic.

## Documentation Policy

- Do not create any `.md` files, documentation, reports, audits, summaries, changelogs, or notes unless the user explicitly requests them.
- Documentation generation is disabled by default.
- By default, provide all results directly in the chat instead of creating files.
- Before creating any `.md` file, verify that the user explicitly requested it.

## When `.md` Files Are Explicitly Requested

- Write the file in English.
- Keep it concise but complete.
- Preserve all important technical details.
- Avoid unnecessary verbosity, repetition, and filler content.
